verbs.description: rescribe (third-person singular simple present rescribes, present participle rescribing, simple past and past participle rescribed)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To write back; to write in reply.
examples: Whenever a Prince on his being consulted by any one rescribes or writes back in this manner, he seems to dispense with that act.

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To write out again; to rewrite.
